om Product Tabs for WooCommerce</a>, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/lj-maintenance-mode/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Maintenance Mode</a>, <a href="https://www.contentviewspro.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Content Views Pro</a>, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/nav-menu-roles/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Nav Menu Roles</a>, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/ewww-image-optimizer/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">EWWW Image Optimizer</a></p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you’re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process, we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin Multilingual Ready.</p>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">WP Hide &#038; Security Enhancer</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Hide and increase Security for your WordPress website instance using smart techniques.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-hide-security-enhancer/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download  WP Hide &#038; Security Enhancer</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">YIKES Custom Product Tabs for WooCommerce</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Add custom tabs to WooCommerce products.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://yikesplugins.com/plugin/yikes-custom-product-tabs-for-woocommerce/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Purchase YIKES Custom Product Tabs for WooCommerce</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Maintenance Mode</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Simple maintenance mode wordpress plugin.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/lj-maintenance-mode/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download Maintenance Mode</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Content Views Pro</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Displays WordPress posts, pages, products, events in layouts (Grid, Pinterest, Masonry&#8230;) without coding!</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://www.contentviewspro.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Purchase Content Views Pro</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Nav Menu Roles</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Hide custom menu items based on user roles.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/nav-menu-roles/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download Nav Menu Roles</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">EWWW Image Optimizer</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Reduce image sizes in WordPress including NextGEN, GRAND FlAGallery, FooGallery and more using lossless/lossy methods and image format conversion.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/ewww-image-optimizer/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download EWWW Image Optimizer</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=IP8EFGgxsyM:tSW8_4w8FGU:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/IP8EFGgxsyM" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/compatible-plugins-oct-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/compatible-plugins-oct-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"WooCommerce Multilingual 3.9";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/GRPLOALovTc/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/woocommerce-multilingual-3-9/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Oct 2016 15:22:54 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WPML versions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://wpml.org/?p=1096376";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:394:"This version packs new functionality, compatibility with the upcoming WooCommerce major release, and improved usability. WooCommerce 2.7 ready WooCommerce 2.7 introduces some code refactoring that required code in our plugin to be updated as well. Some of the areas covered involve coupons and orders. Since WooCommerce Multilingual versions prior to 3.9 will not be fully compatible [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Mihai";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12563:"<p><strong>This version packs new functionality, compatibility with the upcoming WooCommerce major release, and improved usability.</strong></p>\n<h2>WooCommerce 2.7 ready</h2>\n<p>WooCommerce 2.7 introduces some code refactoring that required code in our plugin to be updated as well. Some of the areas covered involve coupons and orders.</p>\n<p>Since WooCommerce Multilingual versions prior to 3.9 will not be fully compatible with WooCommerce 2.7,<strong> we recommend upgrading WooCommerce Multilingual before upgrading to WooCommerce 2.7.</strong></p>\n<p>The 3.9 version of WooCommerce Multilingual will still be compatible with versions of WooCommerce prior to 2.7.</p>\n<h2>New functionality</h2>\n<p><strong>Translate custom taxonomies from the WooCommerce Multilingual page</strong></p>\n<p>Some WooCommerce extensions or themes define custom taxonomies for products. If these need to be translated, they will now appear under on the <strong>WooCommerce </strong>-&gt; <strong>WooCommerce Multilingual </strong>page,  next to product categories, product tags, and attributes.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1097498" style="width: 815px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1.png"><img class="wp-image-1097498 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1.png" width="805" height="331" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1.png 805w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1-150x62.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1-300x123.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-product-taxonomies-1-768x316.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 805px) 100vw, 805px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating custom product taxonomies</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Translate attribute slugs</strong></p>\n<p>Translating attribute slugs allows you to have fully translated filter-like URLs. For instance, if you set the attribute base for your store to &#8220;filters&#8221; (in English), for a global attribute like &#8220;Color&#8221;, the following URL</p>\n<pre>http://example.com/filters/<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>color</strong></span>/black/</pre>\n<p>will display all products having &#8220;black&#8221; as a &#8220;Color&#8221; (either a variation or standard product).</p>\n<p>With WooCommerce Multilingual 3.9 it&#8217;s possible to translate the &#8220;Color&#8221; attribute slug (&#8220;color&#8221;) and have a translated URL like:</p>\n<pre>http://example.fr/filtres/<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>couleur</strong></span>/noir/</pre>\n<p>You can translate the attribute slugs from the <strong>Store URLs</strong> section, on the <strong>WooCommerce </strong>-&gt; <strong>WooCommerce Multilingual</strong> page.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1099500" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs.png"><img class="wp-image-1099500" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs.png" alt="Translating attribute slugs" width="600" height="423" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs.png 875w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs-150x106.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs-300x212.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/translating-attribute-slugs-768x542.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating attribute slugs</p></div>\n<p>Note that an attribute should be marked as translatable and have archives enabled in order to be able to translate the slug for it.</p>\n<p><strong>Use HTML in the currency switcher</strong></p>\n<p>A limited series of HTML tags can be added to the currency switcher template:</p>\n<pre>img span em strong u</pre>\n<p>Besides allowing you to customize how the currency switcher looks, you can also add custom icons for each currency.</p>\n<p>For example, the following template would include icons for currencies:</p>\n<pre class="wikicode prettyprint prettyprinted"><span class="tag">&lt;img</span> <span class="atn">src</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"</span><a href="http://exaple.com/currency-%code%"><span class="atv">http://example.com/currency-%code%</span></a><span class="atv">"</span> <span class="tag">/&gt; %code%\n\n</span></pre>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="attachment_1099559" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-currency-switcher.png"><img class="wp-image-1099559" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-currency-switcher.png" alt="Custom currency switcher" width="600" height="546" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-currency-switcher.png 743w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-currency-switcher-150x136.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/custom-currency-switcher-300x273.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Custom currency switcher</p></div>\n<p>Note that using HTML in the currency switcher is only possible when using the <strong>List of currencies</strong> style.</p>\n<p><strong>Cart total in the currency switcher</strong></p>\n<p>Another addition to the currency switcher is the possibility to include the total of the cart by using the newly available parameter: %subtotal%</p>\n<p>You can set this in the currency switcher template, under the multi-currency options in the backend.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1099580" style="width: 621px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-subtotal.png"><img class="wp-image-1099580 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-subtotal.png" alt="Using the %subtotal% parameter in the currency switcher" width="611" height="302" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-subtotal.png 611w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-subtotal-150x74.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-subtotal-300x148.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 611px) 100vw, 611px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Using the %subtotal% parameter in the currency switcher</p></div>\n<p>This parameter is useful when you want to show the total of the cart in all available currencies. It will display a formatted price so the currency symbol or code doesn&#8217;t need to be added.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="attachment_1097442" style="width: 567px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-total.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-1097442" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-total.png" alt="Showing the cart total in the currency switcher" width="557" height="358" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-total.png 557w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-total-150x96.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/currency-switcher-total-300x193.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 557px) 100vw, 557px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Showing the cart total in the currency switcher</p></div>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2>UI changes</h2>\n<p>Based on the feedback we got from our users, we&#8217;ve made several changes and additions to the backend UI. We think that these represent an important step towards improving the user experience. We also plan to continue these usability improvement efforts in the upcoming releases.</p>\n<p>Over 20 things were touched and here are few of the most prominent changes included in this version:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The setup wizard runs automatically after activation.</li>\n<li>Moved the WooCommerce Multilingual submenu under the WooCommerce menu.</li>\n<li>Added two new subsections to the Status section: products and multi-currency.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2>Compatibility</h2>\n<p>We&#8217;ve fixed <a href="https://wpml.org/forums/topic/woocommerce-booking-price-person-manual-currency-not-working">one more compatibility issue</a> with WooCommerce Bookings where the custom prices were not displayed correctly in the second currency.</p>\n<p>This version address also some issues that were reported about WooCommerce Product Add-ons and WooCommerce Tab Manager</p>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2>Coming up next</h2>\n<p>One long-awaited feature for our plugin is to have <strong>exchange rates that update automatically</strong>. We&#8217;re preparing this for the next release along with more usability improvements, compatibility with more WooCommerce extensions, and more.</p>\n<p>In short, we want to enhance the existing multi-currency functionality by integrating two or three (for now) currency exchange services with our plugin. This will allow having prices in the secondary currencies that are always up to date and without you having to do anything.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="attachment_1099920" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/automatic-exchange-rates_001.png"><img class="wp-image-1099920" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/automatic-exchange-rates_001.png" width="600" height="396" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/automatic-exchange-rates_001.png 755w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/automatic-exchange-rates_001-150x99.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/automatic-exchange-rates_001-300x198.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Configuring exchange rate services</p></div>\n<p>The services that we plan to include in the first phase are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://currencylayer.com">Currencylayer</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/">Yahoo Finance</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://fixer.io/">Fixer.io</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For most stores, regardless of the sales volume or daily traffic, this will not come with an extra cost. These services are either free or include a free plan that includes 1000 request per month, which should be plenty.</p>\n<p>This feature is still in development so, if you have ideas or suggestions we&#8217;d love to hear about it. Please drop a comment at the bottom of this page and share your thoughts with us.</p>\n<h2>Getting the update</h2>\n<p>You should receive this update automatically to the WordPress admin. If you want, you can also download WooCommerce Multilingual from the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WordPress downloads page</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re working hard on making our plugin an important component of WooCommerce based online stores. You can support us by <strong><a href="https://wordpress.org/support/view/plugin-reviews/woocommerce-multilingual?rate=5#postform">rating WooCommerce Multilingual</a></strong> and share your experience with other interested people. Thanks in advance!</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=GRPLOALovTc:sEzRVasl5d4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/GRPLOALovTc" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/woocommerce-multilingual-3-9/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/woocommerce-multilingual-3-9/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Compatible Themes – Oct  2016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/QfsbzwtJOpA/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://wpml.org/2016/10/compatible-themes-oct-2016-2/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Oct 2016 11:01:24 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs"